-- Northam Platinum Says Strike Has Resulted in Lost Revenue of $36.5 Million
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2010-10-06T14:46:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/northam-platinum-says-strike-has-resulted-in-lost-revenue-of-36-5-million.html
Northam Platinum Ltd. said it has
lost about 250 million rand in revenue so far because of a pay
strike at its only mine, Zondereinde, in South Africa.  Workers, on strike for a month now, have lost about 60
million rand, the company said in a statement to the
Johannesburg Stock Exchange News Service today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  